===Adverb===
{{en-adv|-}}

# [[Nevertheless]]; in spite of that.
#:''He told me not to do it; '''however''', I did it.''
# {{context|chiefly|UK}} In [[whatever]] manner.
#:''Do it '''however''' you want.''
# {{context|chiefly|UK|as an intensified form in interrogatives}} In what way; [[how]].
#:'''''However''' did you do that?''

====Usage notes====
* Never use ''however'' when you mean to say ''but''.
* Never use ''however'' at the beginning of a sentence.
* "However" is not a conjunction, but a conjunctive adverb; therefore, when joining clauses with "however", a semicolon must be used and not a comma.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.une.edu.au/tlc/students/factsheets/using-however.pdf| title = Using However | format = PDF | | publisher = Academic Skills Office, [[w:University of New England, Maine|University of New England]]}}</ref>
:''I like chips; '''however''', I detest potatoes.''
* "However" is overused in American English, especially in technical and scientific writing.  It is best avoided.

